Chase is a model-finder for geometric theories.


# Build

  * Run make from terminal.

# Run

  chase

  -i FILE     --input=FILE, --file=FILE	Input theory file
  -d true     --debug	    		Show debug information
  -s bfs/dfs  --schedule=bfs/dfs	Use schedule type (dfs or bfs)
  -b BATCH    --batch			Enable batch processing
  -n true     --incremental		Enable incremental view maintenance
  -1 true     --one			Display only one models (by default,
     	      				the chase builds all models)
  -h          --help			Show help
  -v          --version			Print version


# Remarks

  * --incremental is expected to improve the efficiency of the chase for non-equational
  theories. It significantly hurts the efficiency as the number of equations in the
  theory increases.
  * --batch is buggy.